question: 五つ
sourceMnemonic: From previous number+<ja>つ</ja> words, you can probably guess that this word means <vocabulary>five things</vocabulary>.
sourceReadingMnemonic:
The reading of this word is the kun'yomi reading of the kanji <kanji><ja>五</ja></kanji>, meaning you didn't learn it when you learned the parent kanji reading. To remember this word, think of it this way:

You have <vocabulary>five things</vocabulary>. What do you have to do with them? You need to <reading>eat</reading> (<ja>いつ</ja>) them. If you come up with something crazy you have to eat, and focus on the fact that you must eat five of these things, it will help a lot too.
